{title: Little Joe}
{artist: Hank Snow}
{composer: Written by A.P. Carter, Maybelle Carter, Sara Carter}

I have seen the tears in [F]his honest old [C]eyes
But he said it was the wind that brought them [G7]there
[C]As he gazed on my cheeks growing [F]paler each day
[G7]And his hand went trembling through my [C]hair
Keep tied mother my [F]poor little [C]dog
For I know he'll mourn for me [G7]too
[C]Just keep him when old and [F]useless he grows
[G7]Sleeping the whole summer [C]through
Show him my coat mother [F]so he'll not [C]forget
His master who then will be [G7]dead
[C]Just speak to him kindly [F]and often of Joe
[G7]And pat him on his brown shaggy [C]head
And you dearest mother may [F]miss me for a [C]while
But in heaven I'll no larger [G7]grow
[C]And any kind angel will [F]know at the gate
[G7]When you ask for your darling little [C]Joe